article.headline: A.J. Davis' 2nd half keys UCF's 64-54 win over I-4 rival USF

images.name: C. Perry made Layup. Assisted by J. McMurray.
images.caption: 1H (19:12) USF Chris Perry made Layup. Assisted by Jahmal McMurray.

article.linkText: A.J. Davis' 2nd half keys UCF's 64-54 win over I-4 rival USF
article.story: TAMPA, Fla. -- A.J. Davis scored 20 of his 22 points in the second half and grabbed 10 rebounds to help Central Florida beat I-4 rival South Florida 64-54 on Wednesday night. Davis scored the first eight UCF points of the second half as the Knights took their first double-digit lead at 37-25. UCF led by 13 points midway through the half until Chris Perry's layup cut it to 52-48 with three minutes left. Shaheed Davis and A.J. Davis combined to score the next seven points for a 59-48 lead. The duo scored UCF's final 12 points. Shaheed Davis finished with 15 points for UCF (10-6, 4-1 American). A.J. Davis made 12 of 14 free-throw attempts as the Knights hit 25 of 32 compared to 4 of 11 for the Bulls. Perry led USF (3-17, 0-7) with 18 points and eight rebounds. Jahmal McMurray added 15 points for the Bulls, who have lost nine in a row.

videos.headline: After messy misses, Zeigler finishes with massive dunk
videos.description: USF makes the steal and is on the fast break, but after a pair of misses at the rim, Bo Zeigler cleans up with a powerful one-handed dunk to increase the Bulls' early lead.
